# CODE STANDARDS RULES
## CORE PHILOSOPHY
KISS (Keep It Simple, Stupid), DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself), and maximum readability. Code is read ten times more than it is written.

## NAMING & SEMANTICS
- Use descriptive, intent-revealing names. No cryptic abbreviations (e.g., use `userAccount` over `usrAcc`).
- Naming convention dictates behavior: functions act as verbs (`calculateTotal`), booleans as questions (`isValid`).
- Eliminate magic numbers/strings; extract to globally/locally scoped constants.

## FUNCTIONS & METHODS
- Enforce Single Responsibility Principle (SRP): functions do exactly one thing.
- Keep cyclomatic complexity low. Use early returns (guard clauses) to avoid deep nesting.
- Prioritize pure functions and immutability. Avoid side effects unless explicitly required.

## ERROR HANDLING
- Handle errors explicitly and predictably; never fail silently.
- Throw custom, descriptive errors for domain-specific failures.
- Validate all external inputs at the system boundary before processing.